This paper examines the structure and dynamics of coauthorship, citation, and impact within the CSCW community, which is a multidisciplinary field that involves computer science, information science, cognitive science, and social science. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
